The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Chennai, Nov. 13 (PTI): Police Commissioner R. Sekhar was tonight removed by the DMK government after his force was accused of inaction during the violent student clashes in Dr Ambedkar Law College yesterday in which three students were seriously injured.          
	DGP (Civil supplies) K. Radhakrishnan has been made the new police commissioner                  
	 Mainpuri, UP (PTI): A 16-year-old girl was allegedly raped at gun-point in a village in Mainpuri on Wednesday night. The victim was alone in the house. An FIR has been lodged against two men from the village.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has decided to hear public interest litigations twice a week instead of having just one PIL day on Wednesday. The court said it was getting difficult to hear all PILs in a single day, resulting in many of them getting adjourned without a hearing. Officials have been asked to list pending cases for hearing on Thursdays.                  
	 Vadodara/Ahmedabad (PTI): Gujarat BJP MLA Madhu Srivastav, who was caught confessing in a sting operation that he had paid money to Best Bakery riot case prime witness Zaheera Sheikh to turn hostile, on Thursday resigned from the party. Madhus brother Chandrakant said the state government was unnecessarily harrassing him in a corruption case.                  
	 Madurai (PTI): Madras High Court on Thursday directed the state health secretary to ensure that a three-year-old Dalit boy admitted at a government hospital received necessary treatment. The boys father had accused a clinic of providing wrong treatment to his son.                  
	 Pune (PTI): Dr K.H. Sancheti, an orthopaedist in Pune, has been granted a patent by the Centre for an indigenously designed artificial knee for total knee replacement surgery. The cheaper Indus knee was as good as an imported knee prosthesis, Dr Sancheti said.                                                                                                                         
